[normal]&#xa0;[bold]As way of background, The British Association for Counselling and Psychotherapy (BACP) is the leading and largest professional body for counselling and psychotherapy in Europe, 
[normal]with a membership of 
[normal]over 38
[normal],000 practitioners
[normal], 
[normal]drawn from the various professional disciplines in the field of counselling and psychotherapy and based in a range of settings.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]All BACP members are bound by the Ethical Framework for Good Practice for Counselling and Psychotherapy and within this, the Professional Conduct Procedure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Should the Committee be seeking further oral evidence, BACP would be delighted to provide additional information about 
[normal]psychological therapies long-term conditions.
